IOI Corporation Berhad (MYX: 1961) commonly referred to as IOI, was incorporated on 31 October 1969 as Industrial Oxygen Incorporated Sdn Bhd. IOI is one of Malaysia's biggest conglomerates. It ventured into property development in 1984, followed by oil palm plantations and refineries in 1985. IOI was listed on the Kuala Lumpur Stock Exchange (KLSE)—now known as Bursa Malaysia—in 1980.
The group is headed by Lee Shin Cheng, the executive chairman. Lee Yeow Chor is CEO.
As of September 2016, IOI Group employed more than 30,000 persons from more than 25 countries.
IOI Group's fiscal year runs from 1 July YYYY to 30 June of the following year.
